moved-out-f5-docs-decisions-trust-reconcile-md-implementation-note-356-iteration-1-section-added-recording-the-preflight-s-existence-publishdelivery-s-fail-closed-wiring-and-the-onunderivable-mode-split-with-the-explicit-ci-stays-fail-closed-caveat-confirmed-via-git-diff-independently-re-spot-checked-ac5-no-spawn-and-ac6-publishdelivery-fail-closed-directly-against-the-built-cli-beyond-eval-trust-ac5-s-own-eval-case-sentinel-manifest-override-passed-exit-0-with-the-sentinel-file-absent-ac6-reproduced-directly-with-a-hand-built-unwaived-assumed-session-bundle-against-a-scratch-repo-root-publish-delivery-exited-1-refusing-to-publish-no-delivery-directory-created-and-the-real-repo-s-own-delivery-was-confirmed-untouched-git-status-clean-throughout-a-second-independent-code-review-pass-kontourai-flow-agents-356-plan-work-code-review-iter1-md-verdict-approve-corroborates-this-re-verify-s-findings-its-critique-claim-id-plan-work-code-review-reviewer-tool-code-reviewer-supersedes-the-iteration-0-changes-requested-critique-of-the-same-id-reviewer-pre-existing-disjoint-failures-per-task-instructions-not-356-regressions-independently-re-run-on-this-iteration-1-pass-counts-unchanged-from-the-prior-verify-evals-integration-test-goal-fit-hook-sh-1-issue-goal-fit-hook-should-not-block-by-default-disjoint-from-this-changeset-s-file-set-evals-integration-test-goal-fit-escape-hatch-sh-5-issues-evals-integration-test-session-resume-roundtrip-sh-13-issues-none-of-these-three-files-appear-in-356-s-modified-untracked-file-set-docs-decisions-trust-reconcile-md-docs-fixture-ownership-md-evals-ci-antigaming-suite-sh-evals-integration-test-checkpoint-signing-sh-evals-integration-test-publish-delivery-sh-evals-integration-test-trust-reconcile-negatives-sh-evals-run-sh-kits-builder-skills-deliver-skill-md-scripts-ci-trust-reconcile-js-src-cli-workflow-sidecar-ts-src-tools-validate-source-tree-ts-evals-fixtures-reconcile-preflight-evals-integration-test-reconcile-preflight-sh-scripts-lib-reconcile-shape-js-documented-as-prose-here-not-as-a-standalone-claim-per-the-292-lesson-a-standalone-claim-must-never-be-used-to-launder-a-disjoint-pre-existing-failure-and-this-workstream-s-own-prior-regression-now-fixed-is-likewise-not-re-recorded-as-a-standalone-claim-it-is-folded-into-this-prose-summary-as-fixed-and-independently-reproduced",
      "subjectType": "work-item",
      "subjectId": "kontourai-flow-agents-356/iteration1-fix-and-independent-repro-summary",
      "facet": "flow-agents.workflow",
      "claimType": "builder.pull-work.selected",
      "fieldOrBehavior": "NON-COMMAND SUMMARY (self-checks not independently CI-manifest-registered; the 4 manifest-matched commands above are the reconcilable proof). npm run build --silent compiled cleanly (tsc, exit 0) -- 'npm run build --silent' is NOT itself a manifest/required-lane command (the manifest's legacy fallback tier resolves to 'npm run trust-reconcile-verify', a composite script, not this bare string), so it is prose-only here, not a command-backed claim. bash evals/integration/test_reconcile_preflight.sh (AC1-AC5 proof): all 6 shape cases + CLEAN-BUNDLE (AC4) + AC5 no-spawn sentinel passed, exit 0 -- already re-run inside anti-gaming-and-trust-suite above, not a separate manifest command. bash evals/integration/test_trust_reconcile.sh: TEST 1-4 + YAML-VALID pass, exit 0 (Wave 1 extraction behavior-preservation proof, re-confirmed clean post-fix). bash evals/integration/test_trust_reconcile_negatives.sh: full WS8 negative-regression suite (sections 1-8) PLUS the NEW section 9 (iteration-1 F1 CRITICAL regression guard: hides scripts/ci/derive-claim-status.mjs, asserts CI trust-reconcile.js still exits non-zero fail-closed [9a] while the local reconcile-preflight intentionally degrades to reduced-coverage on the identical bundle [9b]) -- all pass, exit 0. This is the regression eval that would have caught the iteration-0 CRITICAL. bash evals/integration/test_trust_reconcile_manifest.sh: manifest 45 entries == ci.yml --check invocations 45, exit 0 -- parity unaffected by the fix. bash evals/integration/test_publish_delivery.sh: TEST 1-6 pass including AC6 SHAPE-INVALID-REFUSED case, exit 0. bash evals/integration/test_checkpoint_signing.sh: 5/5 test blocks pass, exit 0. All 6 of the individual eval files named above are already members of the anti-gaming-and-trust-suite manifest entry (bash evals/ci/antigaming-suite.sh) re-run above, per AC8's registration-parity design -- listed here for per-file traceability only, not as separate manifest claims. AC1 FIX VERIFIED (this is the regression that FAILED the prior verify pass): scripts/lib/reconcile-shape.js's sessionLocalShapeIssues(sessionLocal, derivedStatus, opts) now takes opts.onUnderivable: 'fail'|'reduce' (default 'fail', the safe/original behavior -- a caller that forgets opts never fails open). scripts/ci/trust-reconcile.js:1172 calls it with { onUnderivable: 'fail' } explicitly (grep-confirmed); src/cli/workflow-sidecar.ts:2771 (runReconcilePreflight) calls it with { onUnderivable: 'reduce' } explicitly (grep-confirmed). INDEPENDENTLY REPRODUCED (not trusting the code-review/fix-plan artifacts alone): hid scripts/ci/derive-claim-status.mjs (moved aside, restored immediately after, git status diffed clean before/after both times), ran the REAL scripts/ci/trust-reconcile.js against the fabricated one-claim session-local pass-asserting bundle (evals/fixtures/trust-reconcile-exploits/status-misassertion.json) with TRUST_RECONCILE_COMMANDS='node -e process.exit(0)': current branch now exits 1 (FAILED -- 1 issue(s) detected, [status-underivable] ... refusing to trust a self-reported status (fail-closed)), byte-identical in message/behavior to a fresh HEAD (pre-#356) baseline run reproduced via a detached git worktree at HEAD (also exit 1, identical output) -- confirming genuine restoration of the pre-#356 fail-closed guarantee, not just a passing eval. F2 (dead branch removed): reconcile-shape.js's sessionLocalShapeIssues is now a clean if/else-if/else with no unreachable inner check (confirmed by direct read, lines 303-337). F3 (log loop consumes shared logEvents): trust-reconcile.js's WAIVED/ATTESTED stdout loop (~1172-1179) now iterates the logEvents/attestedCount returned by sessionLocalShapeIssues itself instead of re-deriving its own parallel classification (confirmed by direct read; only one classification source of truth remains). F4 (helper extracted, <50 lines): checkpointStalenessWarning(dir, repoRoot, tr) extracted as its own function (workflow-sidecar.ts:2704-2727); runReconcilePreflight (2729-2778) is now well under the 50-line guideline (the Q3 ancestor-warning try/catch moved out). F5 (docs/decisions/trust-reconcile.md): 'Implementation note (#356, iteration 1)' section added, recording the preflight's existence, publishDelivery's fail-closed wiring, and the onUnderivable mode split with the explicit CI-stays-fail-closed caveat -- confirmed via git diff. Independently re-spot-checked AC5 (no-spawn) and AC6 (publishDelivery fail-closed) directly against the built CLI beyond eval trust: AC5's own eval case (sentinel manifest override) passed exit 0 with the sentinel file absent; AC6 reproduced directly with a hand-built unwaived-assumed session bundle against a scratch repo-root -- publish-delivery exited 1, 'REFUSING to publish', no delivery/ directory created, and the real repo's own delivery/ was confirmed untouched (git status clean) throughout. A second, independent code-review pass (kontourai-flow-agents-356--plan-work-code-review-iter1.md, verdict APPROVE) corroborates this re-verify's findings; its critique claim (id 'plan-work-code-review', reviewer 'tool-code-reviewer') supersedes the iteration-0 CHANGES_REQUESTED critique of the same id/reviewer. PRE-EXISTING, DISJOINT FAILURES (per task instructions, not #356 regressions; independently re-run on this iteration-1 pass, counts unchanged from the prior verify): evals/integration/test_goal_fit_hook.sh (1 issue: 'goal-fit hook should not block by default' -- disjoint from this changeset's file set), evals/integration/test_goal_fit_escape_hatch.sh (5 issues), evals/integration/test_session_resume_roundtrip.sh (13 issues). None of these three files appear in #356's modified/untracked file set (docs/decisions/trust-reconcile.md, docs/fixture-ownership.md, evals/ci/antigaming-suite.sh, evals/integration/test_checkpoint_signing.sh, evals/integration/test_publish_delivery.sh, evals/integration/test_trust_reconcile_negatives.sh, evals/run.sh, kits/builder/skills/deliver/SKILL.md, scripts/ci/trust-reconcile.js, src/cli/workflow-sidecar.ts, src/tools/validate-source-tree.ts, evals/fixtures/reconcile-preflight/, evals/integration/test_reconcile_preflight.sh, scripts/lib/reconcile-shape.js). Documented as prose here, not as a standalone claim, per the #292 lesson (a standalone claim must never be used to launder a disjoint pre-existing failure, and this workstream's OWN prior regression -- now fixed -- is likewise not re-recorded as a standalone claim; it is folded into this prose summary as fixed-and-independently-reproduced).",
